 Wade. Edelgard E. DuBruck is professor emerita in the Modern Languages Department at Marygrove College, and Barbara I. Gusick is professor emerita of English at Troy University-Dothan, Dothan, Alabama.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCulturexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aFifteenth century. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 4aGerman Literature. 4aMedieval History. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aArt.  aBad Fortune.  aBetrayal.  aFalse Accusations.  aFifteenth-Century Studies.  aGood Fortune.  aLiterature.  aLove.  aManuscript Writing.  aOld Age.  aPhysical Handicaps.  aSexuality.  aWomen's Virtues.1 aAzuela, Cristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoggi, Flavio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoonton, Diane E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBooton, Diane E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClassen, Albrecht, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiller, George T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuBruck, Edelgard E, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuBruck, Edelgard E, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDuBruck, Edelgard E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDufournet, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEven, Yael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerulaitis, Leonardas V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGusick, Barbara I, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHyatte, Reginald, econtributor.4ctb4https:/